nche</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 212<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 1:15:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=522.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: High Level Faction . . .</span><hr size=1> You can't &quot;ruin your faction forever&quot;<br><br>You will probably find yourself switching a few times in your career.<br><br>It's all about which armor quests you want to do in Velious, and since most of it (except for Thurgadin armor) almost requires a guild (yes, I know HoT is quite doable with a couple good groups, not necessarily a guild) your guild will likely dictate which faction you're on at what time.<br><br>But switching faction is something you can do in a couple week's time easily, so don't worry about the possability of &quot;ruining it forever&quot; kuz the Velious factions are designed to be fixable.<br><br><br>What choices are there?<br><br>Dwarf, Giant, Dragon.<br><br>It's pretty easy to be on Dwarf and Dragon factions at the same time... possible to be on Dwarf and Giant... near impossible to be on Giand and Dragon at the same time...<br><br>To raise Dwarf Faction, kill giants (there are some giants in areas of Kael that give only dragon faction)<br><br>To raise Dragon faction, kill giants.  (all giants give a Dragon factoin hit)<br><br>To raise Giant faction, kill dwarves and dragons. (if you kill just dragons you can do the armor quests, but will be KoS in some areas of Kael still)<br><br>It gets more complex when you start talking about the bosses of each race (Dain, Tormax and Yelinak) but I'll just leave say they're all fixable, and arn't really anything to worry about until you find yourself doing one of their *REALLY* high end quests.<br><br><br>Hope that made sense. <p><IMG SRC="http://users.starpower.net/dmoser/images/warlord.jpg" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=200></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhouek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Houek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 1:20:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=522.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: High Level Faction . . .</span><hr size=1> So if I'm on Giant faction, I can run around Kael and the Giants won't kill me?  That's awesome. <br><br>This only applies to Velious?  It won't affect the old world, or Kunark?  Obviously doens't apply to Luclin. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uarative.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arative</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 166<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 1:29:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=522.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: High Level Faction . . .</span><hr size=1> I started off on dorf faction, cause I was raiding kael a lot and thrug is the most complete city on velious in terms of supplies, as a side effect I got ally to dragons as well.<br><br>Later I switched to Gaint faction because I joined a guild that did ntov and got armor for kael quests. <br><br>After I got the armor I wanted, I decided that I wanted to the dain ring quest so I got back my dorf faction.<br><br>Its easy to get any faction in velious and just as easy to change it. Since your closing in of 50, I would recommend going +dorf/cov so you can get armor drops for thrug plate drops <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukaldayrmalabranche.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaldayr Malabranche</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 213<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 1:41:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=522.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: High Level Faction . . .</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> This only applies to Velious? It won't affect the old world, or Kunark? Obviously doens't apply to Luclin.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Yup, this is just a Velious thing... Velious is pretty much a clean slate for all PCs, no outstanding faction problems for evil races and all that.<br><br>Just remember when working on factions:<br><br>There are 2 factions for each city, and 3 for Kael, just because you're not KoS to one, doesn't mean you can't be KoS to another.<br><br>However....<br><br>Skyshrine might as well be only on one faction, because the only thing on Yelinak faction is... well... Yelinak.  (and I've been on Dragon faction forever, and I just saw Yelinak for the first time this week... he's still Scowls : P)<br><br>And in Thurgadin, I don't *think* there's anything in the main city that's on Dain faction, although 